content:
I'm attempting to predict a user's next action based on the current day and time using Microsoft Azure Machine Learning Studio. I have a csv dataset with userid, action, and datetime, and want to train a matchbox recommendation model. However, I can't find a way to use date/time in the training. When I try to get results from the predictive endpoint, the training endpoint returns an error: "ModuleExecutionError: Module execution encountered an error. Error 0018: Training dataset of user-item-rating triples contains invalid data." How can I resolve this error and successfully use date/time in my training model?

Error Code: 
```
{
    "error": {
        "code": "ModuleExecutionError",
        "message": "Module execution encountered an error.",
        "details": [
            {
                "code": "18",
                "target": "Train Matchbox Recommender",
                "message": "Error 0018: Training dataset of user-item-rating triples contains invalid data."
            }
        ]
    }
}
```
